0 DAMAGE~
  DAMAGE
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

When one character attacks another, the severity of the damage is shown
in the verb used in the damage message.  Here are all the damage verbs
listed from least damage to most damage:

    miss        wound           MUTILATE        DEMOLISH
    scratch     maul            DISEMBOWEL      DEVASTATE
    graze       decimate        DISMEMBER       OBLITERATE
    hit         devastate       MASSACRE        ANNIHILATE
    injure      maim            MANGLE          ERADICATE

    More messages may be installed later.
    And, at the far reaches of damaging power, you can do unspeakable
    things.
~

0 COLOR COLORS~
  COLOR COLORS
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

Use the color command to switch between color ON and OFF.

Color is accessed with the ` character.

Just type ` followed by one of the following:

         k - Black   K - Light Black
         y - Yellow  Y - Light Yellow
         g - Green   G - Light Green
         b - Blue    B - Light Blue
         r - Red     R - Light Red
         c - Cyan    C - Light Cyan
         m - Magenta M - Light Magenta
         w - Normal  W - White
~

0 DEATH~
  DEATH                                                   
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

When your character dies, you are reincarnated back at the Altar of
the Temple of Midgaard.  Your corpse is left behind in the room where
you were killed, together with all of your equipment.  Your gold stays
with you.

Any spells which were affecting you are canceled by death.

Following and groups are not affected by death.

You lose experience points for dying.  The amount you lose is half-way
back to the beginning of your level.  Thus if you have a bad day and
die several times, the penalties won't clobber you.

Corpses decay after time, and the objects inside corpses decay with
them. Player corpses last *roughly* 30 hours of game time (15 minutes
of real time). Only the player who died, or someone in the same group,
can retrieve objects from a player's corpse.
~

0 RAISE EXPERIENCE LEVEL XP~
  RAISE EXPERIENCE LEVEL XP
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

Your character advances in power by gaining experience.  The amount of
xp needed to gain a level depends upon how many creation points you
spend during character creation.  

You gain experience by:

    being part of a group that kills a monster

You lose experience by:

    fleeing from combat
    recalling out of combat
    being the target of certain spells
    dying

There is a small amount of random variation in the amount of xp you
recieve from killing a certian mobile, although it is fairly
consistant.

You may type LEVEL or LEVELS at any time in the game to get a listing
of how much xp you need to reach the next 4 levels in the game.

To raise a level, type RAISE when you have negative experience to your
next level.
~

