0 NORTH SOUTH EAST WEST UP DOWN~
  NORTH SOUTH EAST WEST UP and DOWN                         movement 
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
 Use these commands to walk in a particular direction.  You may      
 abbreviate any of these commands with just the first letter.        
                                                                     
 See also: none                                                      
~

-1 BACKSTAB BS~
  BACKSTAB BS                                           combat skill 
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
 BACKSTAB is the favored attack of thieves and other rogues.  It     
 requires you to WIELD some form of weapon.  BACKSTAB can only be    
 used to begin a fight, not during COMBAT.  You cannot BACKSTAB an   
 injured foe unless you are SNEAKing.  BACKSTAB may be abbreviated   
 as simply BS.                                                       
                                                                     
 See also: SNEAK                                                     
~

-1 CHANNELS CHANNEL~
 CHANNELS                                                       info 
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
 Channels are a means of global communication with other players.    
 When you speak on a channel, everyone who is listening to that      
 channel will here you.  Swearing or SPAMming on a public channel    
 may cause an immortal to block you from speaking on or hearing      
 any channels.  This is called nochanneling.                         
                                                                     
 Here is a list of channels currently available on this MUD...       
 AUCTION MUSIC GOSSIP SHOUT YELL INFO QUESTION ANSWER                
                                                                     
 Also, you may type CHANNELS at any time to list which channels you  
 are currently listening to.                                         
                                                                     
 See also: SPAM AUCTION MUSIC GOSSIP SHOUT YELL INFO QUESTION ANSWER 
~

-1 SPAM~
 SPAM                                                           info 
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
 Spam is the act of overloading a CHANNEL or other publicly seen     
 place with lots of text, causing others' screens to scroll by too   
 quickly to be read.  SPAM is considered extremely rude, and if you  
 a player does it in excess, they WILL be punished.                  
                                                                     
 See also: CHANNELS                                                  
~

-1 FOLLOW~
  FOLLOW <name>                                                       
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
 FOLLOW starts you following another character (player or mobile).
 You can only follow someone you can see.  For instance, if the      
 character you are following enters a dark room, and you are not     
 holding a light, you will be unable to follow.  To stop following   
 anyone else, just FOLLOW yourself.                                  
                                                                     
 See also: GROUP                                                     
~

-1 GROUP~
 GROUP <name>                                                        
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
 Players may like to adventure in GROUPs.  Group members share       
 EXPERIENCE points from kills, may SPLIT gold picked up from CORPSEs 
 among the group members, may communicate via the GTELL command, and 
 can AUTOASSIST other group members in COMBAT.                       
                                                                     
 <name> must be FOLLOWing you before you can add them to your group  
 with the GROUP command.  If <name> is already a member of your      
 group, then the command will remove them from your group.           
 Characters may also leave your group by using the FOLLOW command to 
 stop following you.                                                 
                                                                     
 GROUP with no argument shows statistics for each member of your     
 group.                                                              
                                                                     
 See also: EXPERIENCE SPLIT AUTOSPLIT GTELL AUTOASSIST FOLLOW        
~

-1 EMAIL~
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
Syntax: email <address>

This command allows you to set your e-mail address.  Anyone and
everyone has the ability to see someone's e-mail address by 'whois
<name>'.  Someone's email can be unlisted, if they haven't set their
e-mail address.
~

-1 KILL~
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
Syntax: KILL <name>

This command starts battle with a character or mob.  Use this command
carefully!  It may be useful to consider the mob first, before
attacking it.

See Also: consider
~

-1 WORTH~
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
Syntax: WORTH

This is an informational command.  It provides the character's gold,
total experience, and amount of experience until the next level.
~

-1 AFK~
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
Syntax: AFK

Stands for "Away from Keyboard".  Messages will be recorded after
character has switched into AFK mode.  You may turn off or toggle
AFK mode by typing "AFK" again.
~

-1 TRACK~
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
Syntax: track <name>

This command is like hunt. Here is an example.  After typing, "track
bob", it will provide the direction to follow to found "bob".  You
may continue to track a character or mob until you reach the room with
them.
~

-1 AUTOLIST CONFIG~
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
Syntax: autolist
        config

Both autolist and config are the same command. It shows the status of
"OFF/ON" on your auto commands.  And the status of noloot, nosummonj,
nofollow, and color.

See Also: AUTOLOOT, AUTOSAC, AUTOASSIST, AUTOGOLD, AUTOSPLIT,
          NOFOLLOW, NOLOOT, NOSUMMON
~

-1 AUTOLOOT AUTOSAC AUTOASSIST AUTOSPLIT AUTOGOLD AUTOEXIT~
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
Syntax: autoassist
        autoloot
        autosac
        autogold
        autosplit
        autoexit

Use the any auto command to switch between ON and OFF status.

AUTOASSIST allows a character to automatically assist its companions
in battle, when they are grouped.

AUTOLOOT automatically loots a corpse.

AUTOSAC automatically sacrifice a corpse.

AUTOGOLD automatically removes gold from a corpse.

AUTOSPLIT automatically splits the gold between group members.

AUTOEXIT automatically displays the available exits in a room.

Also see: SPLIT
~

-1 NOFOLLOW COMBINE NOLOOT NOSUMMON COMPACT~
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
Syntax: nofollow
        combine
        noloot
        nosummon
        compact

Use the any of these commands to switch between ON and OFF status.

NOFOLLOW prevents other people from following you.

COMBINE provides either a short or long inventory list.  Short list
keeps the same objects together and places a amount of each object
before the object's short name, if more than one object.

NOLOOT prevents thieves from looting your corpse.

NOSUMMON prevents a mage from summoning or any form of transportation
on you.

COMPACT - Will be added later!

All of these commands can be toggled.
~

-1 INFO~
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
Syntax: info

This is information channel and can be toggled.  This channel shows
logs on and off, player deaths, and player leveling.
~

-1 OOC ANSWER QUESTION~
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
Syntax: ooc <message>
        answer <message>
        question <message>

Type a channel name by itself to turn it off.

OOC is an out-of-character global channel.  

ANSWER/QUESTION is an in-character global channel. You may ask
questions, and may receive an answer if someone else is on.

Also see: CHANNELS
~

-1 QUIET DEAF~
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
Syntax: quiet
        deaf

Use the QUIET command to switch between quiet ON and OFF. If you turn
quiet on, you won't be able to hear any global channels. You may only
hear says and see emotes.  Personal messages such as tells will be
recorded.

Use the DEAF command to switch between deaf ON and OFF.  If you turn
DEAF on, you won't be able to hear shouts.

Also see: CHANNELS
~

-1 SEARCH~
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
Syntax: search

Tells you the secret exits of the room you are in.  Not all exits are
visible. You can use the 'bump' technique to find hidden exits.
(Try to walk in a certain direction and see what you bump into).
~

-1 BRIEF~
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
Syntax: brief

Use the brief command to switch between brief ON and OFF.
Turning brief on, it enables short room descriptions.
~

-1 DELETE~
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
Syntax: delete

BE CAREFUL!  First time this command is used.  You can reverse the
deletion status by following the prompted message.  If you use this
command twice, you pfile will be ERASED!

~

-1 OUTFIT~
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
Syntax: outfit

This command provides sub issue equipment up to the level of 5.
~

-1 COMMENT~
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
Syntax: comment <text>

You may use this to provide a pleasant comment to be viewed on
your whois.

See also: WHOIS
~

-1 WHOIS~
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
Syntax: whois <name>

It displays the level, age, and other stats for the given <name>.

See Also: EMAIL COMMENT
~

-1 MESSAGES~
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
Syntax: messages

Retrieves saved messages from being afk or sleeping.
~

-1 TQ~
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
Syntax: TQ

Will be added later!
~

-1 CLAN CLANS~
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

Clan are similar to guilds on other muds.  Most of the clans have
special requirement to join them.  

See Also: JOIN PETITION ACCEPT OFFER RESIGN DEMOTE CRECALL
          PROMOTE SHOW CLANTALK 
~

-1 CLANTALK~
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
Syntax: clantalk <message>

Sends the message to all on-line clan members.

          UNTIL FURTHER NOTICE DON'T USE THIS CHANNEL!

~

-1 SHOW JOIN PETITION ACCEPT DECLINE~
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
Syntax: show <all/inactive/active>
        join <number>
        petition <person>
        offer <person>
        accept
        decline

SHOW ALL lists all clans.

SHOW INACTIVE shows only the clans that are not recruiting.

SHOW ACTIVE shows only the clans that are recruiting.

JOIN <number> attempts to make you join a clan. It will tell you if
you can't join a certain clan, and why.

PETITION <person> petitions to join person's clan.  This is for clans
that do not autoaccept members.

OFFER <person> offers membership in your clan to person.

ACCEPT accepts membership in a clan if it was offered, or accept
someone else's petition to join your clan.

DECLINE same as accept, but refusing the offer.
~

-1 PROMOTE DEMOTE RESIGN CRECALL~
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
Syntax: promote <person>
        demote <person>
        resign
        crecall

PROMOTE <person> promotes a person to higher rank in the clan.
There are 5 ranks.

DEMOTE <person> demotes a person one rank in a clan.

RESIGN type this twice to remove yourself from the clan.
Clan leaders and Sponsors MUST find replacements before doing this.

CRECALL recalls you and your pet if you have one to the clan recall
point. May not work for clans without a clan hall.
~

